author: Mike Santa Barbara
title: Dover tops Polytech, improves to 3-2
text: Dover tops Polytech, improves to 3-2 Comment By Mike Santa Barbara Posted Oct. 12, 2015 @ 9:56 pm The Dover Senators improved to 3-2 on the season, defeating Polytech 43-0 on Monday night. After a tough loss to Smyrna last week, the Senators bounced back nicely in a dominating effort over the Panthers. Dover took control early, building a 23-0 lead after one quarter. The Senators would add two more scores before the first half came to a close, leading Polytech 37-0 at the break. With the lead in hand in the second half, Dover would score once more to give them the 43-0 victory. The Panthers continue to struggle on both sides of the ball, being shutout Monday for the third time this season while falling to 0-5 overall. Polytech will be the guest at another team’s homecoming later this week when they travel north to Baynard Stadium where they’ll take on DMA Friday night at 7 p.m. Dover is also on the road later this week, hoping to keep pace in the Henlopen North taking on divisional foe Cape Henlopen Friday night at 7:30 p.m.
